parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy at all in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the dashboard cracks or has hairline cracks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall has caused a delay in the repair of the airbag system, leaving vehicles with a potentially faulty airbag system that can cause serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the dealer is unable to repair the airbag system due to parts unavailability
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, compromising the safety of the vehicle and its occupants.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
especially in the rear section
near the fuel tank
and on the cross members; holes and flaking in the frame; rusted-out fuel pump housing and high-pressure line.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can lead to compromised airbag deployment and potentially cause injuries to occupants.
symptoms: Cracks in the dashboard
especially near the passenger airbag and instrument cluster; cracks in multiple places; dashboard warping and cracking due to sun exposure or inferior materials.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the interior door handle can lead to inconvenience and potentially cause injuries to occupants.
symptoms: The driver's side interior door handle completely broke off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Stabilitrak and ABS systems can lead to loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Stabilitrak and ABS lights come on
and the vehicle powers down and barely moves; this has happened on several occasions
mostly during cold weather
but also at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission dipstick can lead to inconvenience and potentially cause damage to the transmission.
symptoms: The transmission dipstick broke at the bracket.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump can lead to engine damage and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The oil pump has been replaced and is still not working as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to fail safety inspections, leading to potential safety hazards, such as accidents or collapse of the vehicle, which can result in severe personal injury or death.
symptoms: Frame rust and corrosion
holes in the frame
subframe fracture
failure to pass safety inspections
vehicle instability
and rust on the body rocker panels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can cause the airbag to deploy improperly, leading to potential safety hazards, such as injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Cracking of the dashboard
particularly around the airbag area
and formation of cracks on the passenger and driver sides.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spontaneous combustion of the vehicle can cause fires, which can lead to injuries, fatalities, and property damage.
symptoms: Spontaneous combustion of the vehicle
fire in the cab/bed area
and damage to adjacent properties.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Shaking and rumbling of the vehicle
damage to the molding around the rear passenger wheel well
and tire failure.
